The paper discusses compressed sensing (CS) of physiological signals using a Bayesian learning approach. The paper focuses on the recovery of multichannel signals, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of spatiotemporal correlation, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. The use of Bayesian learning suggests that it may belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. The application of the proposed algorithm to brain computer interface (BCI) and EEG-based driver's drowsiness estimation suggests that it may belong to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-categories.
